{
  "texts": [
    "Evidence that the ensembled classifiers are well-calibrated, and hence learned the likelihood ratio, is provided in Appendix A.Figure 1 shows the results for the tail-cut case.",
    "Ignoring the stochastic nature of the training data, the NP-optimal classifier should be quite singular: all jets with m < 0.17 should have classifier weights given by a delta function at w = 1 -ε, where ε is the fraction of jets removed from the tail.",
    "In addition, there should be a delta function only for reference jets at w = ∞.",
    "A realistic classifier will transform these two features as a smooth weight distribution.",
    "In Fig. 1 we see the smooth weight distribution from our classifier, with nearly all jets populating a sharp peak near one, and a long tail extending to larger values of w, solely in the reference sample."
  ]
}